column5: The black flies are starting to make an appearance up in Haliburton.  water was 45.5 to 52 degrees  by the time I had found warmer water and figured out the walleye, the wind was blowing up and I didn't have long  all fish were caught on suspending twitch baits, I had minnows and worms but they weren't necessary    my walleyes and the slot restrictions didn't jive so I kept 2 of these    how did everybody else do?
No luck with the wallys for me as I was stuck on shore. But I did land this guy
Got blown all over the lake, but managed few smaller ones. My buddy caught one about 17-18".
On Cameron Lake Sunday only a couple of under slot sized fish that went back to get bigger.
Chris,A day out and a feeds a feed. Nice going.  The season has only just begun. Many more days.

Wind helped me find the crappies, absolutely loaded a small bay with 62 degree water.  It was a competition between me and the old man who could catch more       Haven't tried for eyes yet, but there's no rush with thee water temps.
kickin' butt as usual Shawn, nice!
Oh man I've got the itch now.  Can't wait for the opener!
I got out today, finally, for some eyes. Put 7 keepers in the boat with a few under slots, and 2 overs. Great day! Also brought home a great feed of crappies! Life is good again!  S.
